Works with IMAP + Thunderbird.</description><pubDate>Tue, 30 Jul 2013 00:56:36 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://faq.i3wm.org/question/44/email-notification-in-i3/?answer=2305#post-id-2305</guid></item><item><title>Answer by xeen for &lt;p&gt;Can anyone tell about good email notification tools working on i3wm?&lt;/p&gt;
 </title><link>https://faq.i3wm.org/question/44/email-notification-in-i3/?answer=53#post-id-53</link><description>If you use Thunderbird and “set urgent flag” is enough mail notification for you, you can use the “New Mail Attention” add-on. It does have a few options, but it basically just works.</description><pubDate>Wed, 06 Jun 2012 06:55:41 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://faq.i3wm.org/question/44/email-notification-in-i3/?answer=53#post-id-53</guid></item><item><title>Answer by miguel for &lt;p&gt;Can anyone tell about good email notification tools working on i3wm?&lt;/p&gt;
 </title><link>https://faq.i3wm.org/question/44/email-notification-in-i3/?answer=55#post-id-55</link><description>If you use mutt with the `set beep_new` setting, it is possible to activate the urgency hint in xterm or urxvt by adding the following lines to the `~/.Xresources` configuration file:

    XTerm*bellIsUrgent: true
    URxvt*urgentOnBell: true

Then the color of the window decoration will change according to the `client.urgent` colorclass and the workspace button color defined by `urgent_workspace` (see [changing colors](http://i3wm.org/docs/userguide.html#_changing_colors) and [workspace colors](http://i3wm.org/docs/userguide.html#_colors) in the userguide),
when the window is out of focus. This would also work when the beep from the PC speaker is disabled.
</description><pubDate>Wed, 06 Jun 2012 08:26:24 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://faq.i3wm.org/question/44/email-notification-in-i3/?answer=55#post-id-55</guid></item></channel></rss>